        "text": "A-5 First solution: (by Reid Barton) Let r1, . ., r1999 be the roots of P. Draw a disc of radius ε around each ri, where ε < 1/3998; this disc covers a subinterval of [−1/2, 1/2] of length at most 2ε, and so of the 2000 (or fewer) uncovered intervals in [−1/2, 1/2], one, which we call I, has length at least δ = (1 − 3998ε) /2000 > 0. We will exhibit an explicit lower bound for the integral of |P(x)|/P(O) over this interval, which will yield such a bound for the entire integral.",
